text: On tap. Black color, brownish head. Aroma is sweet, syrupy with a hint of dark cherry and deep fried doughnut. Taste has whiskey, maple, burnt sugar and toffee on the aftertaste. Medium, syrupy body, light to medium carbonation. Overly intense, difficult to drink but tasty, quite sweet.

Tap @ Himmeriget. Black with brown head. Aroma is roasted malts, chocolate, coffee, espresso, bourbon, vanilla, maple and liquorice. Flavour is roasted malts, chocolate, coffee, bourbon, vanilla, little espresso, little maple, sweet, warming and a little bitter.
On tap at Himmeriget. Black with a small tan head. Aroma and taste of roasted malt, bourbon, vanilla, toffee, wood and syrup. Sweet and with a full body.
Keg at Himmeriget. Pours neae olaque black with a small brown head. Aroma is maple, chocolate and oak. Taste is maple sweet, cocoa bitter, chocolate sweet, vanilla sweet, oak, fudge:
Tap @ Himmeriget. Black. Burnt, caramel, bacon. Super sweet with vanilla and char. Smooth, just the right body, a bit greasy. Very interesting.

Draught @ Himmeriget. Pours pitch black with a brown head. Aroma of roasty malts, coffee, roasty malts, maple syrup and toffee. Taste is sweet, sticky and syrupy with loads of roastiness, coffee, chocolate, cocoa, vanilla and toffee. Finish is smooth, sweetish and slightly roasty with loads of coffee, chocolate, cocoa, vanilla, oak, bourbon, wood, toffee, syrup and toffee, hints of bacon. Heavy and complex.

From tap at Himmeriget. Fast schwarze Farbe. Geruch is extrem süß schokoladig malzig, karamellig, Vanille, viel Kaffee, bourbon. Geschmack nach Vanille, bourbon, Kaffee, schokoladig, super geil die scheiß..

Tap @ Himmeriget. 
Poured pitch black with a thin brown head. 
Bourbon aroma, some maple, some soy and roasted malts? 
Flavor has maple, sweetness, caramel, malts, bourbon. Balanced. Lovely. Oh the aroma.
Tap at Himmeriget, Copenhagen. Colour is dark brown with small brownish head. Aromas and flavors: Coffee, dark chocolate, some bourbon and roasted malts. Excellent.

Tap @Himmeriget. Black, small light tan head. Heavy syrup and fudge aroma. Bourbon and barrel. Flavour has loads of maple syrup, bourbon warmth. Surprisingly light, but many maple stouts seem that way to me. Lasting finish, maple and licorice with lovely alc warmth.

Tap @ Himmeriget. Black with a brown head. Aroma is sweet, roasted malt, chocolate, maple and bourbon. Flavor is very sweet and rather bitter. Dry and rather bitter finish with lots of warming alcohol. Oily. 110517

Draught @ Himmeriget. Pours black with a brown head. Aroma of sweet roasted malt, caramel, light honey, dark chocolate, coffee, vanilla, wood, bourbon. Flavor is sweet, rich malty, caramel, coffee, chocolate, wood, vanilla, bourbon, alcohol. Medium to full body, soft carbonation, sweet finish with loads of warming alcohol. 110517

Draught. Pitch black coloured. Dense light brown head. Aroma. Sweetness roast herbs coffee liqourice. Flavour. Roast sweetness choco herbs molasses medium to full bodied ends alc dense androastef

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Keg at hime..thingy ma bob...Dark black... Thin tan lacing... Heavy rich dry chocolate roast malts.. Light bourbon nose.. Dark chocolate roast malts.. Heavy chocolate. Dark dry chocolate roast.. Light maple.. Light roast.. Soft coffee chocolate roast malts

Pours dark with minimal head 
Aromas of coffee, maple syrup, muscavado, caramel, chocolate 
Taste has notes of chocolate, maple syrup, some coffee, muscavado, vanilla, caramel

Pours black with oily low tan head. Aroma of bourbon, vanilla, chocolate, light German sausage. Taste is sweet, mild chocolate and chilli, sweet lingering finish. Rich and creamy body with soft carbonation.

Pours black with a low tan head. Aromas of chocolate, smoked meat, caramel, maple syrup, slight leather. Taste is intense woth maple, caramel, lightly smomed meat, vanilla. Mouthfeel is full bodied with low carbonation.

Draft at Himmeriget. Pours pitch black with a small tan head. Chocolate heavy, coffee, maple, cocoa, vanilla, bourbon, molasses, lingering sweetness, light smoke. Bit too much of the cloying maple syrup sweetness. Love the flavor but it losse some of its dimension on it.
On tap at Mikkeller & Friends. Pitch black pour with a tan head. Notes of caramel, maple syrup, chocolate, bourbon, vanilla, light roasted malt. Very sweet and bourbony, a bit too syrupy.
AIBF2016. Viscous black pour with a creamy mocha head. Malty roasty maple bourbon nose. Sweet, tiny bitter and tiny salty taste. Big thick mouthfeel. Big flavours. Nice!

Draft. A black beer with a brown head. The aroma has notes of maple sirup, roasted malt, bourbon, and soy sauce. The flavor is sweet with notes of roasted malt, bourbon, maple sirup, and chocolate, leading to a bitter finish.

UPDATED: FEB 25, 2017 25.02.2017, tap @ Himmeriget:
21.10.2016, tap @ What?s Brewing:
Nice brown slightly bubbly mediumlasting head. Aroma is rich and slightly dry roasted, dark malts, dark sugar, cocoa, salty caramel, licorice, vanilla, coffee, chocolate pudding, oak, bourbon. Taste is rich and slightly dry roasted, dark malts, oak, cocoa, bourbon, coffee, oak, burnt caramel, roasted grain, vanilla, bark, salt, grass, toast, minerals. Medium to longlasting bitterness, slightly boozy and dry roasted mouthfeel. Very nice.

Draught at Himmeriget.
Pitch black colored with a small beige head.
Sweet and roasted aroma of maple syrup, chocolate, oak, bourbon and vanilla.
Sweet and roasted flavor of caramel, maple syrup, bourbon and chocolate.
Roasted finish.

Sweet and light roasted aroma and taste, great mouthfeel, prominent notes of maple sweetness, some caramel, toffee, some chocolate, medium light roasted coffee, very faint meaty nuance going on, sweet malty finish.

Tap @ Himmeriget. Pours pitch black with a small brown quickly dissapearing head. Aromas of deep sweet fudge, sweet maple, light saltiness, roasty coffee, biscotti, vanilla, light booze. Taste is sweet, biscotti, maple, chocolate, vanilla, boozy, some savory and peppery coffeelike notes in the back along with some subtle roast.
From tap. Roasted dark malty and thick malty, roasted. Dark malty and caraemlish. Bitter and roasted. Bitter and dark malty, caramelish and toffee. Sweet caramelish finish.
Tap. Whats brewing 2016. Svart oljeaktig. Lavt karbonert. Smaker eik,røkt bacon,bourbon,lønnesirup,kaffe og mørkbrent malt. Meeget god denne

How: Draught.
Where: All in Beerfest 2016.
Appearance: Black colour with a brown head.
Aroma: Chocolate, vanilla, coffee.
Body: Full body, medium carbonation.
Flavour: Chocolate, coffee, vanilla, a bit sweet.

Draught at All In Beer Fest 2016-11-05, session 2, Göteborg
AR: dark milk chocolate, black rich coffey, wee salty
AP: thick brown fluid, wee dark brown head
F: salty peanuts, heavy and rich fruity coffee, bourbon vanilla, bacon, sweet sugar feeling
